    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Cases or covers, often of cloth and decorated, used to hold the afiqoman, which is a piece broken from the second of the three matsot, set before the leader of a Seder and put aside to be eaten at the end of the meal.</Note_Text>
